  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Resupply Ships are large mobile bases that are used as
  strategic refuelling facilities. They have gas extraction components to m=
ine
  fuel from gas giant planets or gas clouds.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>To build Resupply Ships you must first research them in=
 the
  Energy tech tree. Resupply ships are built at colonies instead of Space
  Ports. Resupply ships can be built 50% larger than your current maximum s=
hip
  construction size.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Resupply Ships need to slowly deploy in order to mine f=
uel
  or to be used for resupply by other ships. When deployed, the resupply sh=
ip
  is immobile &#8211; before moving to a new location they must first undep=
loy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Resupply ships are typically sent to uninhabited system=
s or
  gas clouds and are used by fleets as refuelling points. They are deployed
  deep inside enemy territory, allowing fleets to continue attack missions
  without withdrawing all the way back to their own space ports to refuel.<=
o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>While they are well-defended with weapons and shielding,
  resupply ships can still be vulnerable if discovered by a large enemy for=
ce.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
